The paper describes a method for information extraction from HTML corpus, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The method also involves clustering and unsupervised learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the extracted information can be stored and queried in a database (cs.DB).
